        "content": "<p>Apparently we do not have the category of pointed groupoid, which i needed in a project,  so , in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/15055\">#15055</a> , I define the category of pointed objects of a concrete category, and establish an equivalence to the category of elements of the forgetful functor <code>forget C</code> of the concrete category. This equivalence is used to show that a map of concrete categories induces a functor between the correponding category of pointed objects. </p>\n<p>comments/reviews appreciated.</p>",
        "id": 455342594,
        "sender_full_name": "Sina Hazratpour ð“ƒµ",
        "timestamp": 1722421268
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I left some comments</p>",
        "id": 455356357,
        "sender_full_name": "Dagur Asgeirsson",
        "timestamp": 1722426041
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this is the wrong definition, and there should be no mention of concreteness. If <code>C</code> has an initial object, then <code>Pointed C</code> should just be <code>Under (âŠ¥_ C)</code>.</p>",
        "id": 455508389,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1722470189
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Did you mean terminal instead of \"initial\"? <br>\n<a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/pointed+object\">https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/pointed+object</a></p>\n<p>What I want from <code>Pointed C</code> is that its objects are pairs <code>(X, x)</code> where <code>X</code> is an object of <code>C</code> and <code>x</code> is in <code>X</code>.  So for instance, <code>Pointed Type</code> is a category whose objects are types and an element of the type, or <code>Pointed Grp</code> is a category whose objects are groups and an element of group, say <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>âˆ’</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(\\mathbb{Z}, -2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">âˆ’</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>On the other hand, the under category <code>Under (âŠ¤_ Grp)</code> is <code>Grp</code> itself, which is not what I want. </p>\n<p>Maybe, the name \"pointed objects \" is not good? maybe we want \"objects with a point\"?</p>",
        "id": 455547200,
        "sender_full_name": "Sina Hazratpour ð“ƒµ",
        "timestamp": 1722486968
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(also, sometimes a category might not have a terminal object but is concrete such as the category of fields.)</p>",
        "id": 455547252,
        "sender_full_name": "Sina Hazratpour ð“ƒµ",
        "timestamp": 1722487020
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will add that you should feel free to refactor <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Pointed#doc\">docs#Pointed</a></p>",
        "id": 455547536,
        "sender_full_name": "YaÃ«l Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1722487250
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Yes, I should have said terminal.)</p>",
        "id": 455570627,
